  "response_text": "The average weekly consumption of whole milk per agent starts at approximately 2600 units at the initial time step. There is a sharp decline in consumption within the first five steps, dropping to around 1000 units. This rapid decrease suggests a significant shift in consumer behavior away from whole milk early in the simulation period. 

